{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10103", "repo": "rails", "body": "How about this for the first one:\r\n\r\n> As you can see, you can generate mailers just like you use other generators with Rails. Mailers are conceptually similar to controllers, and so we get a mailer, a directory for views, and a test.\r\n> \r\n> If you didn't want to use a generator, you could create your own file inside of `app/mailers`, just make sure that it\r\n> inherits from `ActionMailer::Base`: \r\n\r\n```\r\nclass MyMailer < ActionMailer::Base\r\nend\r\n```", "_id": {"$oid": "5237e31bbd3543c1510090bd"}, "issue_id": 10103, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/16066114", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10103#issuecomment-16066114", "updated_at": "2013-04-08T17:43:10Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik", "login": "steveklabnik", "gravatar_id": "233c279c012ebac792aaa805f966cbc7", "html_url": "https://github.com/steveklabnik", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/233c279c012ebac792aaa805f966cbc7?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F0c22d45f31acf0f4192c8c12b7a55dee.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 27786, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2013-04-08T17:43:10Z", "id": 16066114, "owner": "rails"}
